name: Reebok Ragnar Great River
intro:
Reebok Ragnar Relay Great River brings together the magic of running through rural and urban Minnesota, bonding with new and old friends, and the accomplishment of conquering 200 miles by foot. Your team of 12 (or 6) will start your running adventure on the bank of the Mississippi River in Winona. From there you’ll experience every shade of green you can imagine as you run by endless rows of corn fields and through forested areas like Afton State Park. There’s no shortage of water views on this course including sunset views on Pepin Lake. Come be a part of 10+ years of history at Ragnar Great River and learn what it means to Find Your Inner Wild! 

GREAT NEWS! All 2017 Reebok Ragnar Relay captains will be receiving free Reebok  running shoes!! As a captain, we know you are committed to going the distance and Reebok wants your feedback. Check out our Reebok Shoes page for more info!

Great River is just around the corner. Make the weekend even more meaningful by fundraising for a Ragnar charity partner or your favorite charity on everydayhero, the official fundraising platform of Ragnar Relay Series! 

Simply go here (or click on the everydayhero logo above) and choose your favorite charity – it’s that easy!  Your fundraising page will be created and you can start making every step count.

To date, the Ragnar community has fundraised over 1 million dollars so let's keep it going! 

Questions? Email nonprofits@everydayhero.com.

We’re very excited that Team Bolder Options is back with us for the 6th year as the signature charity of the Great River Relay!  Bolder Options provides young people at risk of going down the wrong path with the opportunities, guidance and support to help them make the right turn. Youth are matched with a caring adult mentor and introduced to an active-lifestyle based program that provides guidance, support, and opportunities through one-on-one, small group, and family specific activities designed to help them make positive choices and live a healthier life.

If you ran Great River in 2015, it’s a good chance you ran next to one of the Running Team members of Team Bolder Options, wrapped your lips around some delicious pancakes and sausage at the Exchange 30 or enjoyed an ice cold brew at the finish line beer tent served up by a helpful member of their Volunteer Team.  Team Bolder Options’ runners & volunteers raised a ton of money that helped their youth mentoring program reach more than 3,700 youth and families in Minneapolis, St. Paul and Rochester, MN in 2015.

Through our partnership, Team Bolder Options is offering you a special opportunity to “B BOLD” and join their team in 2016. Running and Volunteer teams that join Team Bolder Options for the Reebok RAGNAR Great River Relay can get FREE or DISCOUNTED ENTRY into the race AND earn special INCENTIVE BONUSES by hitting their “fundRACING” goals! Efforts to reach these goals go a long way in helping Bolder Options inspire greatness in the lives of youth and families that need them the most. 

Click here to learn more about creating, or joining a RAGNAR Great River Relay team on behalf of Team Bolder Options and help inspire greatness in more youth like this.

Join the Team and “B RAGNAR BOLD”!

travel.name: Hotel Options
travel.content:
Hotel Options

We have partnered with onPeak to provide you with hotel options for your race. Through this partnership, we are able to offer you the most competitive nightly rates at favorable hotels throughout the city and will strive to provide you with a smooth and effortless booking process when making your travel reservations. Book Early with Our Official Lodging Partner for the Best Selection!

Click HERE to view onPeak's special hotel offers for Reebok Ragnar Great River participants! 


 

Van Rental

Need to rent a van? Enterprise can hook you up!

 

Elevated Legs Rental

Turn your van into a recovery station! Our partners Elevated Legs are renting legs for $120 for the whole race - that's $20/person for a van of 6!

For more information check out: http://elevatedlegs.com/rent/ragnar/

*Be sure to rent your legs before Monday, August 8th to ensure delivery before the race!*

reg_system.name: Reebok Ragnar Great River
reg_system.description: Reebok Ragnar Relay Great River brings together the magic of running through rural and urban Minnesota, bonding with new and old friends, and the accomplishment of conquering 200 miles by foot. Your team of 12 (or 6) will start your running adventure on the bank of the Mississippi River in Winona. From there you’ll experience every shade of green you can imagine as you run by endless rows of corn fields and through forested areas like Afton State Park. There’s no shortage of water views on this course including sunset views on Pepin Lake. Come be a part of 10+ years of history at Ragnar Great River and learn what it means to Find Your Inner Wild!
